## Atomicity Rules

### MUST have one primary component per file

Each file MUST export exactly one main DDD component (entity, value object, use case, service, repository, etc.).

**Exceptions:**
- Small helper types/interfaces (< 20 lines) used only within that file
- Related DTOs that are tightly coupled to the main component
- Private helper classes used only within that file

### ✅ CORRECT - One component per file

```typescript
// packages/events/domain/value-objects/email.ts
// ✅ One primary export: Email value object

type EmailValidationResult = {
  isValid: boolean
  error?: string
}

export class Email {
  private constructor(private readonly value: string) {}

  static create(value: string): Email {
    const validation = this.validate(value)
    if (!validation.isValid) {
      throw new OneJsError('Invalid email', 400, validation.error)
    }
    return new Email(value.toLowerCase())
  }

  private static validate(value: string): EmailValidationResult {
    // Validation logic
    return { isValid: true }
  }

  toString(): string {
    return this.value
  }
}
```

```typescript
